		<h2 class="text-3xl border-b-2 mt-5 border-black">Article III: Judicial Branch</h2>
		<h3 class="mt-5 text-xl">Section 1</h3>
		<p>
			The federal judicial power shall be vested in a Supreme Court, and in inferior courts
			established by the Expenditure Congress. The judges, both of the Supreme and inferior courts,
			shall receive a compensation for their work, which shall not be reduced during their tenure.
		</p>
		<h3 class="mt-5 text-xl">Section 2</h3>
		<p>
			Each State legislature shall appoint one Supreme Court Justice to serve for a 20-year term
		</p>
		<h2 class="text-3xl border-b-2 mt-5 border-black">Article VII</h2>
		<p>
			To hold any constitutionally recognized office a person shall be at least 25 years of age. No
			person shall hold more than one constitutionally recognized office at a time. No person shall
			serve more than two four year terms in any constitutionally recognized office.
		</p>
